ICT futureObjectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give overview about geographical aspects and effects of the distribution of ICT; to describe main methods of spatial positioning and structure of respective datasets, to introduce using of positioning data in scientific research and development of location based services.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course the students: *	Will be able to understand content of ICT geography and key theories *	Understand main effects of ICT on the societal and personal level *	Will be able to describe main spatial positioning methods, applications and spatial accuracy *	Are aware of the principles how location based services work and what are the main application areas *	Will be able to understand privacy and security risks related to the ICT; are aware of legal aspects *	Be knowledgeable with forecasts for the future of ICT
